AB  - Building operations account for about 30 % of global final energy use, underscoring the need for intelligent, data-driven energy management. Modern building automation systems generate vast volumes of real-time time-series data from heterogeneous sources, yet non-technical users often face high entry barriers due to fragmented metadata, inconsistent APIs, and complex query languages. To address these challenges, we present PV-GPT, an agent framework that leverages large language models (LLMs) and the Brick ontology to enable natural language querying of building energy data. By integrating structured prompting, modular primitive functions, and a closed-loop retrieval–generation–execution architecture, PV-GPT translates user queries into accurate, executable code across semantic (SPARQL), API, and time-series databases. The system is evaluated using a real-world dataset collected from 60 rooftop photovoltaic (PV) systems at the Hong Kong University of Science and Technology, accessed via the SolarEdge API. Additionally, we construct a synthetic question-answering dataset comprising over 1000 diverse temporal and semantic query tasks for performance testing. Typical end-to-end response time ranges from 2 to 6 s, corresponding to human–computer interactivity rather than hard real-time control, with latency primarily arising from LLM inference and external API response delays. Experimental results show that PV-GPT achieves a task-solving accuracy of 98.14 %, significantly outperforming baseline prompting approaches. The system consistently generates syntactically correct, executable Python scripts aligned with real-world data schemas, demonstrating strong generalizability and operational reliability. This work contributes: (1) a novel LLM-agent framework tailored to real-time building data access; (2) a structured prompting method integrating semantic models and code primitives; (3) and a validated QA dataset supporting systematic evaluation. These results illustrate the potential of LLM-driven agents to democratize building analytics, reduce dependence on manual scripting, and support scalable, real-time decision-making in smart building environments. The demo video of PV-GPT can be viewed at https://youtu.be/iEYb6x8OcnQ.
